ccommodate greater platform play, and involves combat against waves of enemies using the Werehog\'s brute strength.','Tomoya Ohtani','Sonic Team','','Play Station 2','Sega (PS2, Wii, Xbox 360, PS3)','D:~Games~Play Station 2~ROMS~Sonic Unleashed (USA) (En,Ja,Fr,De,Es,It).iso','','','','','2008-11-18','PCSX2',1,'2018-12-16 03:17:16',0,'2019-01-25 12:23:38',0),(170,'Sonic Heroes','Action, Platformer',1,'No',0,'PCSX2','USA','Sonic Heroes is a 3D platformer.[1] While the preceding Sonic Adventure games for the Dreamcast featured elements of action-adventure and exploration, Sonic Heroes focuses on linear platforming and action,[2][3] similar to the Sonic the Hedgehog games for the Sega Genesis.[4] The story is also simpler than those of the Sonic Adventure games. In it, series antagonist Doctor Eggman threatens to use a weapon to destroy the world and sends out legions of robots. Four groups of three characters from the franchise\'s history separately team up to put a stop to Eggman\'s plans.[5] The player navigates using one of the teams, who serve as the player characters.[2] The teams consist of Sonic the Hedgehog, Miles \"Tails\" Prower, and Knuckles the Echidna; Shadow the Hedgehog, Rouge the Bat, and E-123 Omega; Amy Rose, Cream the Rabbit, and Big the Cat; and Espio the Chameleon, Charmy Bee, and Vector the Crocodile, respectively.[5] Each team has its own campaign, called a story.[6] Each also represents a different difficulty. Amy\'s team, for example, is designed for beginners, while Shadow\'s is aimed at experienced players.[4]','Jun Senoue','Sonic Team USA','Takashi Iizuka','Play Station 2','Sega','D:~Games~Play Station 2~ROMS~Sonic Heroes (USA) (En,Ja,Fr,De,Es,It).iso','','','','','2003-12-30','PCSX2',1,'2018-12-16 03:20:30',0,'2019-01-25 12:14:56',0),(171,'Silent Hill Origins','Survival Horror',1,'No',0,'PCSX2','Japan','The objective of Silent Hill: Origins is to guide player character, Travis Grady, as he searches the monster-filled town of Silent Hill for